    {
      "id": "sybil_13_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_13",
      "description": "Available for the discerning driver is a 2003 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine. This naturally aspirated power plant utilizes six individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS variable valve timing to deliver a broad power band and sharp throttle response. Power is sent to the rear wheels via a crisp 6-speed manual gearbox and a factory limited-slip differential. This example has undergone critical preventative maintenance, including rear subframe reinforcement and a VANOS system overhaul, ensuring the chassis handles the torque loads expected of this platform. The suspension retains its factory-tuned balance, offering precise turn-in and excellent damping characteristics. While the exterior reflects its history as a driven machine, the mechanical vitals\u2014including compression and oil pressure\u2014remain within optimal operating parameters. A",
